  "texts": [
    "The network is applied to homogenization tasks of RVEs [522,523], where the material of the phases is varied during evaluation.",
    "Neural differential equationsIn a more general setting, neural ordinary differential equations [402] consider the forward Euler discretization of ordinary differential equations.",
    "Specifically, RNNs are viewed as Euler discretizations of continuous transformations [524][525][526].",
    "Consider the iterative update rule of the hidden states y t+1 = y(t + t) of a RNN.y t+1 = y t + f (y t; θ) (75)Here, f is the evaluation of one recurrent unit in the RNN.",
    "In the limit of the time step size lim t → 0, the dynamics of the hidden units y t can be parametrized by an ordinary differential equationdy(t) dt = f (y(t), t; θ) (76)The input to the network is the initial condition y(0), and the output is the solution y(T) at time T. The output of the NN, y(T), is obtained by solving Eq. 76 with a differential equation solver."
